The article discusses the anniversary of the Holodomor, a man-made famine in Ukraine caused by Joseph Stalin and the Soviet regime in 1932-1933. It highlights how millions of Ukrainians suffered and died due to starvation as a result of the regime's policies. The article also mentions the current conflict between Ukraine and Russia, with Russian forces deliberately targeting Ukraine's agricultural infrastructure to weaken its economy and independence. It argues that this not only affects Ukraine but also poses a threat to global food security. The article calls for remembrance of those who suffered in the past and support for Ukraine in its fight against tyranny, as well as a commitment to preventing suffering and protecting human rights.